  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The interaction between the intervention condition and T1 loneliness was significant for perceived supervisor emotional support (b =.07, SE =.03, p <.05, ß =.10, pseudo DR 2 =.01), indicating that the intervention effect depended on levels of T1 loneliness (see Table 4).",
    "Similarly, the hypothesized moderation effect of intervention and T1 loneliness on perceived supervisor destigmatizing behavior was significant (b =.09, SE=.03, p <.01, ß =.13, pseudo DR 2 =.02).",
    "We explored the interactions in two ways.",
    "First, we generated conditional effects graphs depicting the intervention effect on the outcome for each level of the moderator variable (i.e., baseline loneliness) (Bodner, 2017).",
    "The form of the interaction is similar for emotional support and destigmatizing behavior (Figure 1a and b, respectively)."
  ],
